name: compute
description: The extent to which code consumes CPU compared to other possible solutions to the same requirement.

name: correctness
description: Does the implementation produce the correct output for a range of carefully selected inputs.

name: robustness
description: The tolerance of a solution to corner cases that may lead to unstable solutions or failure to complete a calculation. One example might be to consider whether it works well for pathological inputs (e.g. sorted arrays for quicksort, or really large floating point numbers).

name: memtotal
description: The extent to which code consumes RAM.
